Package: scx-switcher
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: SCX Switcher <scx-switcher@local>
Installed-Size: 198
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.34), libgcc-s1 (>= 3.0), libqt6core6t64 (>= 6.8.2), libqt6gui6 (>= 6.4.0), libqt6network6 (>= 6.1.2), libqt6widgets6 (>= 6.3.0), libstdc++6 (>= 5), polkitd, scx-scheds (>= 1.1.0), scx-tools (>= 1.1.0)
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Description: Qt6 GUI for managing sched-ext BPF schedulers on Debian 13+
 SCX Switcher is a Qt6 GUI that lets you install, switch, and monitor
 sched-ext BPF CPU schedulers (scx_bpfland, scx_lavd, scx_rusty, ...).
 .
 The scx-scheds and scx-tools packages provide the scheduler binaries and
 scx-loader/scxctl runtime. This package only provides the GUI.
 .
 Once installed, the GUI provides:
  - One-click scheduler start, stop, and switch
  - Live status display with auto-refresh
  - Boot persistence toggle (scx_loader.service)
  - Scheduler reference cards with descriptions and supported modes
  - System tray integration with status indicator
